==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thermotension
<hw>Ther`mo*ten"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thermo-</ets> + <ets>tension</ets>.]</ety> <def>A process of
increasing the strength of wrought iron by heating it to a determinate
temperature, and giving to it, while in that state, a mechanical strain
or tension in the direction in which the strength is afterward to be
exerted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermotherapy</ent>⟦br⟧
